cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract geospatial information from textual narratives. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to identify toponyms and spatial relationships, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to quantify and reason about object locations, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories. Finally, the paper deals with geospatial data, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category as well.
